# NOTE: .claudeignore is an unofficial feature — works in practice but not guaranteed by Claude Code
# See: https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/579
#
# Status:
# - Security-related exclusions moved to settings.json permissions.deny
# - Token optimization exclusions remain here as .claudeignore works in current versions
# - Migration strategy: docs/claudeignore-migration.md
#
# Original: Aggressive Token Optimization v1.2.0
# Excludes EVERYTHING except core essentials
# Command-specific modules are loaded on demand (see conditional-loading.md)

# LARGE META-DOCUMENTATION (Load on demand via @load directive)
# These are about token optimization itself, rarely needed
# Migration: GAP — design docs have no official exclusion mechanism
.claude/rules/intelligent-prefetching.md    # 21KB - Phase 4 prefetching system
.claude/rules/module-caching.md             # 17KB - Phase 3 caching strategy
.claude/rules/module-priority.md            # 14KB - Phase 2 priority loading
.claude/rules/conditional-loading.md        # 11KB - Loading rules documentation

# Reference documents (load on demand)
# Migration: DONE — YAML frontmatter alwaysApply: false (all reference files now have frontmatter)
.claude/rules/*/reference/
.claude/**/reference/

# ALL detailed rules (load on demand based on task/context)
# Migration: DONE — all rule files have YAML frontmatter with alwaysApply: false and paths

# Operations rules (only for cleanup/monitoring tasks)
.claude/rules/operations/

# Project management rules (only for build/testing tasks)
.claude/rules/project-management/

# API design rules (only for API development tasks)
.claude/rules/api/

# Coding standards (only for code implementation, not for workflow commands)
.claude/rules/coding/concurrency.md      # Load: concurrent/thread tasks
.claude/rules/coding/memory.md           # Load: memory leak/crash debugging
.claude/rules/coding/performance.md      # Load: optimization tasks
.claude/rules/coding/error-handling.md   # Load: bug fixing, implementation
.claude/rules/coding/quality.md          # Load: code review, refactoring

# Security rules (only for security-related tasks)
.claude/rules/security.md                # Load: auth, security, vulnerability tasks

# Testing rules (only for test-related tasks)
.claude/rules/testing.md                 # Load: test writing, debugging

# Documentation rules (only for documentation tasks)
.claude/rules/documentation.md           # Load: README, API docs, comments

# Keep only core workflow
# .claude/rules/core/ - ALLOWED (essential)
# .claude/rules/workflow/git-commit-format.md - ALLOWED (essential)
# .claude/rules/workflow/github-issue-5w1h.md - ALLOWED (essential)
# .claude/rules/workflow/github-pr-5w1h.md - ALLOWED (essential)

# Exclude workflow reference docs
# Migration: DONE — YAML frontmatter alwaysApply: false
.claude/rules/workflow/reference/

# Agents (load when needed)
# Migration: DONE — on-demand loading is built-in
agents/

# Skills (load when needed)
# Migration: DONE — on-demand loading is built-in
skills/

# MCP template (example only, not active config)
# Migration: VERIFY — may not be loaded as context by default
.mcp.json.example

# Settings
# Migration: VERIFY — settings are parsed by Claude Code, not injected as context
settings.json
settings.local.json

# Documentation
# Migration: GAP — no official way to exclude specific files from context loading
README.md
README.ko.md
TOKEN_OPTIMIZATION.md

# NPM cache
# Migration: .gitignore (transient data)
.npm-cache/
**/.npm-cache/

# Backups
# Migration: .gitignore (transient data)
*.backup
*.bak
*.tmp
